The paper deals with data processing inequalities for sequences, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of bounded Turing functionals also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the study of mutual dimensions between sequences, which is a concept related to data structures (cs.DS).
